{"questionId":"13341","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The plane <em>П</em><sub>1</sub> contains the points P(1, 6, −7) , Q(0, 1, 1) and R(2, 0, −4).</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The Cartesian equation of the plane <em>П</em><sub>2</sub> is given by <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x - 3y - z = 3\">\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mn>3</mn>\n  <mi>y</mi>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mi>z</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>3</mn>\n</math></span>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The Cartesian equation of the plane <em>П</em><sub>3</sub> is given by <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"ax + by + cz = 1\">\n  <mi>a</mi>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mi>b</mi>\n  <mi>y</mi>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mi>c</mi>\n  <mi>z</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>1</mn>\n</math></span>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Consider the case that <em>П</em><sub>3</sub> contains <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"L\">\n  <mi>L</mi>\n</math></span>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Given that <em>П</em><sub>3</sub> is equally inclined to both <em>П</em><sub>1</sub> and <em>П</em><sub>2</sub>, determine two distinct&nbsp;possible Cartesian equations for <em>П</em><sub>3</sub>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>attempt to find scalar products for&nbsp;<em>П</em><sub>1</sub> and <em>П</em><sub>3</sub>,&nbsp;<em>П</em><sub>2</sub> and <em>П</em><sub>3</sub>.</p>\n<p>and equating&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{3a + b + C}}{{\\sqrt {11} \\sqrt {{a^2} + {b^2} + {c^2}} }} = \\frac{{a&nbsp;- 3b - c}}{{\\sqrt {11} \\sqrt {{a^2} + {b^2} + {c^2}} }}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>3</mn>\n      <mi>a</mi>\n      <mo>+</mo>\n      <mi>b</mi>\n      <mo>+</mo>\n      <mi>C</mi>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <msqrt>\n        <mn>11</mn>\n      </msqrt>\n      <msqrt>\n        <mrow>\n          <msup>\n            <mi>a</mi>\n            <mn>2</mn>\n          </msup>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>+</mo>\n        <mrow>\n          <msup>\n            <mi>b</mi>\n            <mn>2</mn>\n          </msup>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>+</mo>\n        <mrow>\n          <msup>\n            <mi>c</mi>\n            <mn>2</mn>\n          </msup>\n        </mrow>\n      </msqrt>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mi>a</mi>\n      <mo>−</mo>\n      <mn>3</mn>\n      <mi>b</mi>\n      <mo>−</mo>\n      <mi>c</mi>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <msqrt>\n        <mn>11</mn>\n      </msqrt>\n      <msqrt>\n        <mrow>\n          <msup>\n            <mi>a</mi>\n            <mn>2</mn>\n          </msup>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>+</mo>\n        <mrow>\n          <msup>\n            <mi>b</mi>\n            <mn>2</mn>\n          </msup>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>+</mo>\n        <mrow>\n          <msup>\n            <mi>c</mi>\n            <mn>2</mn>\n          </msup>\n        </mrow>\n      </msqrt>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Accept&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"3a + b + c =&nbsp;a - 3b - c\">\n  <mn>3</mn>\n  <mi>a</mi>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mi>b</mi>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mi>c</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mi>a</mi>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mn>3</mn>\n  <mi>b</mi>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mi>c</mi>\n</math></span>.</p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\" \\Rightarrow a + 2b + c = 0\">\n  <mo stretchy=\"false\">⇒</mo>\n  <mi>a</mi>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mn>2</mn>\n  <mi>b</mi>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mi>c</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>0</mn>\n</math></span>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>attempt to solve&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"a + 2b + c = 0\">\n  <mi>a</mi>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mn>2</mn>\n  <mi>b</mi>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mi>c</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>0</mn>\n</math></span>,&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"a + 2b&nbsp;-&nbsp;5c = 0\">\n  <mi>a</mi>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mn>2</mn>\n  <mi>b</mi>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mn>5</mn>\n  <mi>c</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>0</mn>\n</math></span>,&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"5a - 7c = 4\">\n  <mn>5</mn>\n  <mi>a</mi>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mn>7</mn>\n  <mi>c</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>4</mn>\n</math></span>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\" \\Rightarrow a = \\frac{4}{5}{\\text{,}}\\,\\,b =&nbsp; - \\frac{2}{5}{\\text{,}}\\,\\,c = 0\">\n  <mo stretchy=\"false\">⇒</mo>\n  <mi>a</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mn>4</mn>\n    <mn>5</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>,</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mi>b</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mn>2</mn>\n    <mn>5</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>,</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mi>c</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>0</mn>\n</math></span>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>hence equation is&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{4x}}{5} - \\frac{{2y}}{5} = 1\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>4</mn>\n      <mi>x</mi>\n    </mrow>\n    <mn>5</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n      <mi>y</mi>\n    </mrow>\n    <mn>5</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>1</mn>\n</math></span></p>\n<p>for second equation:</p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{3a + b + C}}{{\\sqrt {11} \\sqrt {{a^2} + {b^2} + {c^2}} }} = - \\frac{{a&nbsp;- 3b - c}}{{\\sqrt {11} \\sqrt {{a^2} + {b^2} + {c^2}} }}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>3</mn>\n      <mi>a</mi>\n      <mo>+</mo>\n      <mi>b</mi>\n      <mo>+</mo>\n      <mi>C</mi>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <msqrt>\n        <mn>11</mn>\n      </msqrt>\n      <msqrt>\n        <mrow>\n          <msup>\n            <mi>a</mi>\n            <mn>2</mn>\n          </msup>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>+</mo>\n        <mrow>\n          <msup>\n            <mi>b</mi>\n            <mn>2</mn>\n          </msup>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>+</mo>\n        <mrow>\n          <msup>\n            <mi>c</mi>\n            <mn>2</mn>\n          </msup>\n        </mrow>\n      </msqrt>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mi>a</mi>\n      <mo>−</mo>\n      <mn>3</mn>\n      <mi>b</mi>\n      <mo>−</mo>\n      <mi>c</mi>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <msqrt>\n        <mn>11</mn>\n      </msqrt>\n      <msqrt>\n        <mrow>\n          <msup>\n            <mi>a</mi>\n            <mn>2</mn>\n          </msup>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>+</mo>\n        <mrow>\n          <msup>\n            <mi>b</mi>\n            <mn>2</mn>\n          </msup>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>+</mo>\n        <mrow>\n          <msup>\n            <mi>c</mi>\n            <mn>2</mn>\n          </msup>\n        </mrow>\n      </msqrt>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\" \\Rightarrow 2a - b = 0\">\n  <mo stretchy=\"false\">⇒</mo>\n  <mn>2</mn>\n  <mi>a</mi>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mi>b</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>0</mn>\n</math></span></p>\n<p>attempt to solve&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"2a&nbsp;-&nbsp;b = 0\">\n  <mn>2</mn>\n  <mi>a</mi>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mi>b</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>0</mn>\n</math></span>,&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"a + 2b&nbsp;-&nbsp;5c = 0\">\n  <mi>a</mi>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mn>2</mn>\n  <mi>b</mi>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mn>5</mn>\n  <mi>c</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>0</mn>\n</math></span>,&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"5a -&nbsp;7c =&nbsp;4\">\n  <mn>5</mn>\n  <mi>a</mi>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mn>7</mn>\n  <mi>c</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>4</mn>\n</math></span>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p>⇒<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"a = - 2\">\n  <mi>a</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mn>2</mn>\n</math></span>,&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"b = - 4\">\n  <mi>b</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mn>4</mn>\n</math></span>,&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"c = - 2\">\n  <mi>c</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mn>2</mn>\n</math></span>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>hence equation is&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"- 2x - 4y - 2z = 1\">\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mn>2</mn>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mn>4</mn>\n  <mi>y</mi>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mn>2</mn>\n  <mi>z</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>1</mn>\n</math></span></p>\n<p><em><strong>[7 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"13341","referenceCode":"19M.2.AHL.TZ2.H_11d.ii","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Given that П3 is equally inclined to both П1 and П2, determine two distinct possible Cartesian equations for П3.","paper":"2","level":"HL","questionNumber":"d.ii","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 7]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","AHL 3.17—Vector equations of a plane","Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","AHL 3.18—Intersections of lines & planes"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}